    'body' => 'Jesse is correct.  I talked to two guys on our SWAT team...they ***NEVER*** 
drop a weapon (as in physically drop it to the ground.)  They have their 
primary weapon, normally an SMG or Shotgun type weapon, and at least one side 
arm as back up.  If the primary somehow becomes useless, the officer will 
sling it and use his/her back up.  As Special Forces generally have even 
better training than many SWAT teams, I would think that it is even less 
likely....in a building clearing scenario anyway....that they would just drop 
a weapon if it went in-op.  Also I\'m told by the SWAT guys that if anyone on 
the team ran out of ammo for their primary weapon, then either the mission 
was not planned out very well with all contingencies taken in, or the officer 
really screwed the pooch and didn\'t follow his/her instructions for gearing 
up.  Just my .03333333cr worth.

