I agree the "no LH2" requirement could revolutionize starship propulsion...
if it could be duplicated.

I may have mentioned before that the Annic Nova was used in our old gaming
club. The rationalization for it not needing LH2 was that it was connected
to a stable normal-space bubble in jump space. Jump bubbles formed by
normal jump drives decay after a week, but the Annic Nova\'s stayed
indefinitely and could be used again and again. Such stable jump bubbles
were extremely rare and valuable natural phenomena which could not be
manufactured.

