Yeah that makes a whole lot more sense than what I said. Huh, that\'s what
you get for a civie trying to talk service.
Come to think of it, as per above, the SG\'s used to blow the locks then they
switch to a precision weapon upon entry.  

I\'m pretty sure about the releasing the primary when dry (and yeah I think
they said it was on a sling or some such) and going for the secondary as
opposed to reloading, on the basis that it was a lot faster to yank a new
weapon and fire than to reload the old. Though this scenario was to do with
a surprise entry into a drug den as opposed to entry after a siege, so I
guess that changes the rules a tad.

Honestly I\'m not talking pooh, however I could be relaying misheard pooh.

BTW I got so many ailments that conscription can be bandied about as long as
